# World Models

## What are World Models

A world model is a model that learns to represent how the environment evolves in space, time and under actions. 
It often predicts future states or rewards of actions. They are often used in RL, simulations, planning, robotics and most
recently peaked my intrest with the release of [genie-3](https://deepmind.google/discover/blog/genie-3-a-new-frontier-for-world-models/)
that creates stunning interactive environments from short textual prompts. 

Key concepts for world models are: representation learning, dynamics modeling and dealing with 
estimating impact of actor actions on the environment. 

## Why are World Models exciting

They enable exciting new directions like embodied reasoning. 
Include examples of most recent results. 

