## Evolution of World Models

(add diagram)

Work [World Models](https://arxiv.org/pdf/1803.10122) is one of the earlier works that clearly illustrates what is a world model.  
It uses VAE (add link) to encode compact image representation, then models temporal dynamics with an RNN (add link) and trains a controller that gives
actor tools to interact with the environment. It even utilizes to use created environment to train downstream ML models. 

Next interesting work is [Recurrent World Models Facilitate Policy Evolutio](https://arxiv.org/pdf/1809.01999) that extends 
the work with insights on how compact policies can work with learned features and dynamics. 

[Contrastive Learning of Structured World Models](https://arxiv.org/pdf/1911.12247) adds compositional structure of objects and 
relations with contrastive learning (explain later). 

// [Mastering Diverse Control Tasks through World Models](https://www.nature.com/articles/s41586-025-08744-2?) (recent work on scaling to many tasks. Read and include if worth it)



